modules.description: This module supports operations for constructing, modifying, and querying key-value maps, including adding, removing, and merging entries, with functions tailored for ordered keys and sequence-based manipulations. It works with maps featuring string or ordered keys and generic values, enabling tasks like data aggregation, configuration management, and structured transformations. Specific use cases include efficient lookup in ordered datasets, filtering key-value pairs, and combining maps through iterative or recursive processes.

manages key-value mappings with support for ordered and sequence-based operations, enabling addition, removal, and merging of entries. It handles string or ordered keys with generic values, facilitating data aggregation and configuration management. Operations include efficient lookup, filtering, and map combination through iterative or recursive methods. Examples include building structured data from sequences and merging multiple configuration maps.

Handles remote execution requests, manages GUI protocol interactions, and enables reading/writing to a VM's QubesDB database. Operates on serialized message formats, GUI event structures, and key-value pairs stored in QubesDB. Used to launch applications remotely, establish graphical sessions, and persist VM-specific configuration data.

manages key-value pairs with ordered and sequence-based operations, supporting string or ordered keys and generic values for flexible data handling. It enables efficient insertion, deletion, and merging of entries, along with filtering and iterative data combination. Users can construct structured data from sequences or combine multiple configuration maps. For example, it can merge network settings from different sources or build a consolidated IP address table.
